title: Disappointing
text: I have been to almost all the restaurants at Cyber Hub, so for a change we went there. But I was really disappointed with the very limited menu, quality and service. I really expected more from this place. So I won’t visit this place again.

title: Good Hotel with excellent location
text:
This hotel is centrally located with good connectivity with metro. The hotels offer all the services that any business traveller or leisure traveller will look for. Closer to India Gate, Parliament House, Connaught Place.

They offer a delicious buffet breakfast with a wide variety and they have a bar and different restaurants to satisfy your taste buds.

On top of it, the staff is very good.

title: Good Ambience and Music
text: The wine and company offer you excellent service along with tasty food, cocktails and mocktails. I have visited this place on several occasion, and I can recommend this place for an evening outing.

title: Great Location and good hotel
text: I have stayed in this hotel on several occasions. Last year my husband and I stayed at this hotel once again. The hotel is close to Buckingham Palace and many other sights seeing places. There is a good Indian restaurant which is next to it in case you are craving for the Indian Food. The rooms are bit small in size.
place: St. James Court, A Taj Hotel, London

title: Nice place with great cocktails
text: My friend and I went there yesterday evening. Ambience was nice and best part was there vodka based signature cocktails. I tried two different types and both tasted very good. Even food menu was good.

title: Good Hotel with Metro connectivity
text: The hotel is good and provides all the basic amenities. It’s closer to Metro station, so the commuting becomes easier. You get free WiFi and water. The breakfast buffet menu is good. They keep an Indian spread also. We stayed in this hotel during Christmas, so this was fully occupied. Overall good stay.

title: Delicious Food
text: I love Cheesecake Factory. You order anything out of their menu and the food is very delicious. I have been to this place several times, but food never disappoints me. Though you have to wait for a long time on Thursday, Friday and Saturday for your number.

title: Good beach with clean water
text:
I loved the water in this beach. You have ample restaurants around which provides beach beds with different pricing. There is a particular restaurant around this beach which I personally found to be a cheater. They charge 50 Euro’s for the beach bed and they will offer you that you can drink or eat worth 50 Euros from their restaurant for paying for beach bed. You will order just one drink and they will say that your 50 Euros are over.

But beach is nice for sure

title: Not that great
text: I found Little Venice just an ok place. This area has lot of restaurants and other market area which makes it worth a visit.

title: Not that great
text: I personally didn’t find anything much interesting about this place. But Mykonos any which ways does not have much to offer except good beaches and the night life. So you will end up visiting all these places, as you don’t have much choices.

title: Good Insight into Greek History
text: There was a long line to buy the tickets for Acropolis, though I managed to buy skip the line for the Acropolis museum tickets. As we visited this place in mid July hence weather was little warm. But all the wait was worth going up the hill to see the Acropolis. Good insight into history And you can see entire Athens city from the top. A must visit place.

title: Small beautiful Area
text: Plaza is very close to Monastiraki Flea Market, Ifestou, Athens, Greece. My husband and I went to Monastiraki first, once we entered Plaka we could see visibly more beautiful streets which are more walkable and have some street cafes and restaurants. One should visit atleast once.

title: Gateway to Greek History
text: If you are intentionally know or learn about Greek History then you must visit this place. The museum provides you free WiFi and they have food court on the top.

title: Crowded but lively place
text: When we decide to visit Monastiraki Flea Market, Our taxi driver told us to take care of our bags and mobile phone due to some snatching cases. The market is full of silver jewellery, shoes and cotton clothes shops. Good place to shop some local stuff. One should know how to do the bargaining. This place is full of cafes, restaurants and is closer to Acropolis. So you get a good view also.

title: Average Place
text: I and my friends went there for Lunch yesterday. Though the food was average, but the air conditioning was not working properly. So we couldn't enjoy the place.

title: Good selection of Sundae
text: I personally like their ice cream shakes and fruit sundaes. I have eaten here atleast 5-6 times in the last few months and I like everything that they serve.

title: Excellent location with beautiful view
text: My husband and I stayed here for 3 nights. I just loved the place. This has beautiful view, central location and owner of the villa is very nice. I highly recommend this place. Lot of good places to eat and just 15 minutes walk from the main town.

title: Average Hotel
text: The hotel has good big rooms. The hotel is also located in a good location. But the breakfast spread is really disappointing and the service is also slow. The view from the balcony was not very good. Overall ok.

title: Beautiful Hotel with excellent service
text: My husband and I stayed at this hotel for one day. We got a very spacious beautiful room with great view. The staff at front desk was very polite and very efficient house keeping service. They have one beach bar which was good, along with two terrace restaurants. Only thing is that due to close proximity to lake and due to summer season there were too many mosquitoes that were in room as we kept our door open. As we were staying in a non Ac room. But overall great experience.

title: Great location with excellent hospitality
text: This was the first city that we visited in Switzerland during our trip. Hotel has a great location and there was a beautiful view from our terrace. I must like to thank the hotel manager who on our request gave us this lovely room. They provide you complimentary drop and pick upto nearest railway station. Hotel staff was also polite. Neat and clean room.
place: Hotel Royal St. Georges Interlaken - MGallery Collection

title: Nice hotel with good staff
text: Overall Hotel is nice. The street is little quite in comparison to other streets. But located about 15 minutes walk from Eiffel Tower and the Champs Elysees a fashionable avenue in Paris. Though we got a upgrade done but room size was small. Breakfast was not worth its price. The best part was friendly staff of the hotel. Though we reached around 9am at the hotel, but still we got the room.

title: Beautiful but very crowded
text: The Eiffel Tower and its nearby area is beautiful. But there are long queues. So better to buy skip the queue pass. I would definitely visit it again.

title: Historical and combination of beauty
text:
I loved this museum. When you reach this place you feel that you have gone back to history. Great architecture and museum is so big that you need at least 3 to 4 hours to visit each and every floor. The roofs are beautiful and I am
Impressed with the way historical items are preserved and presented in the museum, A must visit.

title: Disappointing
text:
I was really disappointed with the show. I really had some high expectations as I read lot of good reviews about it. We see better performances on TV than the one shown by them. They just have some top less pretty females nothing else. I only like one couple who performed on the stage, they were really good. But they just don't have any theme, few random
Performances. I won't recommend this to anyone.

title: One of the most beautiful regions in Switzerland
text: I stayed in Interlaken for 3 days which comes under Jungfraujoch region. The entire area is beautiful with blue lakes and lush green areas. We went upto Jungfraujoch top, it was a wonderful experience over all. I recommend everyone to visit this place.

title: Small interesting Hill top
text: You can go upto Harder Kulm by 10 minutes train journey and on your way to the top you can see interlaken. Beautiful view from the top.

title: Nice place with good view
text: Hooters Interlaken is located at the right place in Interlaken next to the Main Street. Good food and drinks you get here. Only challenge sometimes is to get a table of your choice. As this place is generally crowded in the evening.

title: Hotel with good rooms, but overall avaerage facilities
text:
I really had higher expectations from this hotel. But this turned out to be an average hotel with slightly different concepts in room in terms of interior. They have poor spread in breakfast with very limited choice.

As hotel has two clubs and one bar, so on Friday to go to your room you have to wait long for lift, as they block three lifts for their club guests. Not meant for families with kids.
place: V Hotel Dubai, Curio Collection by Hilton

title: The most tasty cheese cake i have ever had
text: I must say excellent place with delicious food. Even though there was a long waiting of 45 minutes being Friday, but it was worth the wait. Large portions, good service with friendly staff with extensive menu to select food as per your taste buds. I highly recommend this place to everyone.

title: Good for families
text: We were staying at Atlantis, so we got the opportunity to visit here. Nice place for families with kids with some interesting rides. Also some adventurous rides for adults.

title: Great Music, good food
text: Nice place to spend some time, with good food and nice music. The way they serve food is interesting, accompanied with some gigs that their staff does occasionally.

title: Excellent place to enjoy good food
text: I have been to K3 on number of occasions and this place never disappoints me with its exotic range of food in buffet. Great ambience, excellent food. I would highly recommend this place.

title: Very unfriendly place
text: I was at Smaaash for New Year Eve 2017 party with my family. Half of the games were close in the arcade. Very bad arrangement over all. Bad music. DJ was very rude, when we told him to change the music he called us rude in front of everyone. One of the worst place I have ever visited for New Year Eve's party. I will highly recommend everyone not to visit this place.

title: Average pocket friendly hotel
text:
Hotel is centrally located. But being a old hotel, room service and cleanliness is not maintained properly. They served very poor collection of breakfast buffet and half of them were tasteless.

If you are looking for pocket friendly average priced hotel, then you can go and stay in it. Don't keep very high expectations from it.

title: Nice place to learn some history
text: I visited Sheesh Mahal with my family. We took a local guide who explained the entire history of this place. I must say beautiful place.

title: Beautiful centrally Located Hotel
text:
I stayed here with my husband for two nights. Hotel is centrally located with beautiful lobby and good rooms. Breakfast selection was average in comparison to many other hotels of same category. One important thing I would like to point out is that front desk staff is not very friendly. Even though we requested for an early checkin about a month back, but still when i reached the hotel around 12:00noon, I was refused early checkin and I was told that I have to wait till 3:00pm and incase I wanted I room early they told me to pay 1500 bhats plus taxes extra for an upgrade and for a ready room. I have travelled globally and this was first time that I was given such a reason.

I might not stay again in this hotel.

title: Nice hotel with good view
text: Hotel is nice with beautiful sea view. There is hardly any night life at the Hotel. Pool is good. Wifi does not work in their only operational restaurant, which is not good. Breakfast selection was good. They can have better English speaking waiters, as communicating with half of them was difficult. Quality of Toiletries was bad.

title: Small old Hotel with good staff
text: I must say even though hotel is small and even rooms are not that great, but staff is very friendly, which makes this hotel worth staying. We stayed here for 4 nights and thoroughly enjoyed our stay. Hotel provides all the basic amenities that we require as a traveller. Most of the hotels in Boracay are beach front including this, with great view.

title: Value for Money, exceptionally beautiful rooms
text: I loved this hotel, even though i stayed here for just two nights. Your room balcony opens to a a great sliding pool view. Rooms are located on hill, you have to walk little bit, but still worth it. Hotel is very near to Kata beach, which is one of the best family beach with lot of activities to do and good restaurants and bars nearby. I would definitely like to stay here again.

title: Good Hotel in a Small Town
text: I stayed in this Hotel for one night. Overall I will rate this hotel as a good hotel in a small town. Staff is friendly. Food is average. Rooms are small,but clean. Breakfast was average, they can really improve it. Hotel has no in house taxi facility.
place: Regency Sameera Vellore By GRT Hotels

title: Lunch with VIT students
text: I had lunch at Vellore Kitchen with my son's classmates from VIT. Food was very good, but bit spicy. I tried local non veg Thali, food was just too good

title: Old Hotel with Great View
text: I stayed in this hotel last year for 4 days during our business conference. Hotel location is good, with great view of Windsor Castle. Rooms are small with limited facilities. Food was average. staff was also not very efficient. Next time I might not stay in this hotel again.

title: Two days business conference at Sofitel
text: We organised two day business conference of 150 pax each day at Sofitel on 12 and 13 July, 2016. The banquet and sales staff was very effective. Quality of food was also good. Smooth flow of services, right from the time my team and I checked into the hotel. I must say Helpful staff and great hospitality. I would definitely stay here again and host me future events also in this hotel. I would like to recommend Monal Prabhu from the sales team, Abu Choudhary from the banquets team and Ruhi at the front desk check in counter for making our experience memorable.

title: Pleasure Trip
text: One of the most luxurious hotel, with great river front view. Good food, excellent rooms and services. I would definitely like to go and stay here again. Exotic assortment of breakfast items imaginable; It truly was a very nice first class experience. The management in this hotel are top notch and focus on their guests.

title: Holiday Trip
text: Hotel is located at the right place. So most of the places to see are at the walking distance. Some very good places to eat nearby. It a small hotel with small rooms and average breakfast. Hotel staff is courteous.

title: Holiday Trip
text: Beautiful big rooms.Helpful staff, they went out of their way to make our stay comfortable with them. They gave us complimentary cake, Champagne and wine collection during our stay. Breakfast area was over crowded with limited choice for food.

title: Centrally Located
text: My husband and I stayed at this hotel last year. Location is good. One can walk and see lot of tourist places around the hotel. Small room. But breakfast selection was very good with excellent spread. Staff was helpful and courteous.

title: Beautiful property, very good and efficient staff
text: I stayed in this hotel for 5 days. Its a very beautiful property, staff is very friendly and efficient service. Beach is neat and clean. Very good view. Chef Rohit in the India restaurant is really good. Only thing is that if you love clubbing it is little isolated.

title: very clean water
text: good beach, enjoyed spending day on the beach side and crystal clear water. Hotel provides excellent beachside service.
